    public class ResourceTask<T extends com.anylogic.engine.Agent>
extends com.anylogic.engine.Agent
implements ResourceTaskDescriptor<T>
    Defines some custom task for resources that cannot be defined using the provided standard patterns for failures, maintenance, breaks, etc in the ResourcePool parameters.

      boolean mayPreempt​(T unit)
      Sets whether 'End of shift' task may preempt the task currently being executed, if any.
      In other words, 'true' means that unit will "drop its work" right at the moment of its shift end.
      If 'false', then the unit will finish all its tasks with less priority.
      Note that 'true' option has exceptions: current unit task may have a "non-interruptable" option NO_PREEMPTION.

      'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends.
      void onFinish​(T unit, ResourceUnitTask task)

      ResourcePreemptionPolicy preemptionPolicy​(T unit)
      Specifies the policy for 'End of shift' task preemption:
      NO_PREEMPTION - cannot be preempted (unit will "take a rest" until its new shift begins)
      TERMINATE - may be preempted and will be terminated (unit may be "woken up" during its off-shift time)

      'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends
      double priority​(T unit)
      Sets the priority of 'End of shift' task.

      • PP_NO_PREEMPTION

        public static final ResourcePreemptionPolicy PP_NO_PREEMPTION
        The unit task cannot be interrupted by any high priority task. Unit will "take a rest" until its new shift begins.

      • PP_TERMINATE

        public static final ResourcePreemptionPolicy PP_TERMINATE
        The unit task will be interrupted by any task with higher priority and will be terminated (forgotten). Unit may be "woken up" during its off-shift time.

      • mayPreempt

        public boolean mayPreempt​(T unit)
        Sets whether 'End of shift' task may preempt the task currently being executed, if any.
        In other words, 'true' means that unit will "drop its work" right at the moment of its shift end.
        If 'false', then the unit will finish all its tasks with less priority.
        Note that 'true' option has exceptions: current unit task may have a "non-interruptable" option NO_PREEMPTION.

        'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends.
        Specified by:
        mayPreempt in interface ResourceTaskDescriptor<T extends com.anylogic.engine.Agent>

      • preemptionPolicy

        public ResourcePreemptionPolicy preemptionPolicy​(T unit)
        Specifies the policy for 'End of shift' task preemption:
        NO_PREEMPTION - cannot be preempted (unit will "take a rest" until its new shift begins)
        TERMINATE - may be preempted and will be terminated (unit may be "woken up" during its off-shift time)

        'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends
        Specified by:
        preemptionPolicy in interface ResourceTaskDescriptor<T extends com.anylogic.engine.Agent>
